Over one third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren weigh above the average and 5% are obese.
As the current research shows, obese children come from families who have a unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows again how important the environment in which the human being evolves and the models around it is.
At the tables of obese children, for example, carcuterie 50% more often than in families of children with normal weight.
19% of obese people had dinner fries according to the survey carried out with awareness-raising action "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In small-scale families sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most of today's schoolchildren - only 15% replied that at least once a week parents found time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last year of school and attended 900 primary schools in Czechia.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", a action supported by General Health Insurance and Unilever.
Since the beginning, more than 12000 students from sixth to third have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that causes a dramatic increase in the number of children in overweight, or even obese, is the absence, of proper diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast-in case - lunch - tasting- dinner, which is a basic principle of good food", says one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast and catering for dinner
Experts draw attention to the fact that in order to have healthy development, you need some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In Czechia, only 23% of students' families eat at the same time.
In most families each takes his breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been found is that one tenth of the population doesn't eat breakfast at all.
Yet breakfast is the basis for a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that obese children's families are more often consumed with unhealthy fries.
Almost every student - not to mention the weight - drinks drink every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children asked make sport regularly but for parents it is only half, only 15%.
Get your food ready.
Another part of the survey enabled selected children (204 boys and 172 girls in 13 schools) to prepare their own food on the basis of opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15 are far from the ideal for a healthy diet."
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of cakes, meats and sugars.
"The most alarming is particularly a great preference for sweet lemonades", is indicated in the results of the investigation.
For lunch are the pasta that took the first place right in front of the white meat.
Children did not want to be fertilized and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Head of Health
The investigation also showed that children are prepared to change their habits from the time they receive ad hoc information.
"In the course of a review of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session "Obesity is not a coincidence," a determined commitment was made to go to a healthy diet," the results of the investigation were reported.
The most significant was, for example, with regard to sweet lemonades, as children have begun to give preference to drinking water.
Children have mostly checked white meat and fish as a main dish on the questionnaire and would reduce sugar and knedliky (Czech specialty of bread flour or potatoes).
