History of a brand:
The innovative IBM begins the second century of its existence
If someone was to look for the word that expresses the IBM strategy as close as possible, the closest would be "the long term".
For a large audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, it is a firm felt as very present and yet since its creation it has passed a hundred years.
The foundation of this long-term strategy was laid by the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that many of the world's problems can be solved as long as people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE'!" became the fingerprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to edit in 1935).
It was the basis of the company's culture carefully developed by Watson.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years because it remained faithful to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This allowed us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more"has delayed for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to deal with his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM's people were the only first American employees to have paid vacations, insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and custodians.
Similarly IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
Society was at the beginning brilliant in the discovery of talent - as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and thus could have the choice.
The current plan is entirely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy as it will be a woman- Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano with the head of IBM.
It has been working at IBM for thirty years and is currently in the position of Chief of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has done what is called jamy, brain-storming online from what come many future strategies and innovations.
It is not surprising that there are many ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500000 people who work.
An institution with a good name
