On the same November 9, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the Local Legislative Power and qualified as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the state's representative for constitutional reforms, because he does not have the right to "sanction or contest them".
Interviewed on the possibility of "voting by vote", María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that with the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of IEM it will be possible to make the partial and total discounts of votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial count of votes, one or more electoral packages, may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no poll record and count in the ballot file is not in the chair; or there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total count of votes received in all polls may be made when there is an index of the fact that the difference between the alleged successful candidate of the respective election and the one who obtained the second place in the poll is equal or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition by the representative of the party and/or coalition who presented the second of the candidates reported.
The total voter count may also take place if, at the end of the joint count, the difference between the alleged winner candidate and the second-place candidate is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is the express petition of the representative of the political party whose candidate has gone out second, in which case the electoral packages that were subject to the partial voter shall be excluded.
